        "\n",
        "# US Jobs Growth Craters, Sending Shockwaves Through Markets\n",
        "The big story of the day is the US labor market, which has suddenly shown significant signs of cracking. The Non-Farm Payrolls report for July came in at just 73,000, a huge miss from the expected number and a sharp slowdown from previous months. To make matters worse, the reports for May and June were revised down by a combined 258,000 jobs, suggesting the labor market was much weaker than previously thought.\n",
        "This report is the first hard data point to suggest that the series of aggressive tariffs implemented by the Trump administration are beginning to bite into the real economy. The market reaction was severe: equity futures immediately turned negative, and government bond yields plunged as investors priced in a higher probability of a FED rate cut."
      ],
